section.section:
"Political subdivision" includes:
A county;
A municipal corporation in the State;
A special taxing district in the State; and
A public corporation of the State.

text.section:
A report under this section shall include the affidavit of the financial officer and all of the following information that applies to the political subdivision:
The assessed valuation of taxable and tangible property in the political subdivision;
The total indebtedness of the political subdivision;
The following categories of the total indebtedness:
Bond indebtedness that is redeemable from the proceeds of general and ad valorem taxes;
Temporary or floating indebtedness;
Obligations that are incurred in anticipation of tax collection;
Current bills payable;
Contingent liability that results from the guaranty of an obligation of another political subdivision; and
Self-liquidating bond indebtedness;
As to self-liquidating bond indebtedness:
The amount of indebtedness for each project; and
The source of the revenue for its liquidation;
As to each sinking fund for retirement of obligations:
Each obligation for which the fund is established;
The amount of the fund; and
The manner in which money in the fund is invested;
As to the tax levy for the fiscal year for which the report is made:
The amount of the levy imposed;
The amount of the levy collected; and
Separate items for:
The amount of any special assessment levied; and
The amount of that assessment collected;
As to the tax levy for each of the 3 fiscal years immediately preceding the fiscal year for which the report is made:
The amount of the levy imposed; and
The amount of uncollected taxes;
As to the population of the political subdivision:
The population in the most recent federal census; and
Any official or unofficial population estimates for the fiscal year for which the report is made;
A copy of the most recent actuarial report on the pension system of the political subdivision, unless it is a county or municipal corporation and a member of the State pension system;
As to all categories of indebtedness:
Variable interest rate debt instruments;
Interest rate exchange agreements or swaps; and
Other derivatives, including futures and options; and
Any other information about the financial affairs of the political subdivision that the Department finds pertinent or appropriate and necessary to show accurately the financial condition of the political subdivision.
